CLEAN ROOM IMPLEMENTATION
==========================

This library is a clean room implementation of numerical linear algebra algorithms.
To maintain permissive licensing, GPL-licensed source code (including SLICOT Fortran
sources) was NOT consulted during implementation. All algorithms are implemented from
academic papers, textbooks, and permissively-licensed reference code.

ACADEMIC AND REFERENCE SOURCES
===============================

Sylvester Equation Solvers (src/sylvester/)
--------------------------------------------

Implementation based on:

1. Academic Publications:
   - Bartels, R.H. & Stewart, G.W. (1972). "Solution of the Matrix Equation
     AX + XB = C". Communications of the ACM, 15(9), 820-826.
     DOI: 10.1145/361573.361582

   - Golub, G.H. & Van Loan, C.F. (2013). "Matrix Computations" (4th Edition),
     Section 7.6.3: The Bartels-Stewart Algorithm. Johns Hopkins University Press.
     ISBN: 978-1421407944

   - Jonsson, I. & Kågström, B. (2002). "Recursive blocked algorithms for solving
     triangular systems—Part I: one-sided and coupled Sylvester-type matrix equations".
     ACM Transactions on Mathematical Software, 28(4), 392-415.
     DOI: 10.1145/592843.592845

2. Reference Implementation:
   - LAPACK dtrsyl.f and dtrsyl3.f (LAPACK 3.11.0)
     Copyright (c) 1992-2023 The University of Tennessee and The University
     of Tennessee Research Foundation. All rights reserved.
     Copyright (c) 2000-2023 The University of California Berkeley. All rights reserved.
     Copyright (c) 2006-2023 The University of Colorado Denver. All rights reserved.
     Licensed under BSD-3-Clause (see below)
     Available at: https://netlib.org/lapack/

     Used as reference for: numerical stability patterns, overflow prevention via
     scaling factors, handling of quasi-triangular real Schur form (1×1 and 2×2 blocks),
     and BLAS-based triangular system solving.

3. SLICOT Usage (Documentation and Test Cases Only):
   SLICOT (Subroutine Library in Systems and Control Theory)
   Copyright (c) 2020, SLICOT
   Licensed under GPL-2.0
   Available at: http://www.slicot.org/

   SLICOT ROUTINES REFERENCED (documentation and test cases only):
   - SB04MD: Continuous-time Sylvester equation (Hessenberg-Schur method)
   - SB04QD: Discrete-time Sylvester equation (Hessenberg-Schur method)

   **IMPORTANT**: Only SLICOT documentation (slicot/doc/*.html) and test suite
   (slicot/examples/) were consulted. SLICOT Fortran source code (slicot/src/*.f)
   was NOT examined during implementation to avoid GPL contamination. SLICOT test
   cases provide non-copyrightable facts: numerical test data and expected accuracy
   criteria.

4. Validation References:
   - MatrixEquations.jl (Julia package)
     Copyright (c) 2017-2024 Andreas Varga and contributors
     Licensed under MIT License
     Available at: https://github.com/andreasvarga/MatrixEquations.jl

     Used for: Cross-validation of numerical results in test development

